METHODS Thirty-five children with > or =40% total body surface area burns were randomized to receive either placebo or oxandrolone (0.1 mg/kg by mouth twice daily) from postoperative day 5 to 1 year postburn. Levels of constitutive proteins and acute phase proteins were measured at admission; at discharge; and at 6, 9, and 12 months after burn. Total albumin supplementation and hepatic transaminases were also assessed
